There are 5 main types of creational patterns. 

1) Singleton pattern: The idea behind this pattern is to make sure
that only one object of any class is instanitated. This is done by
making the constructors private and having a static method that
returns the object of the class, that has been instantiated when the
class loads.

2) Factory pattern: The idea here is to provide an object that decides
which object to return based on the data that is provided to it. That
is done by having a class called the 

* Pointer: Try to use composition over inheritance.


